1
00:00:08,067 --> 00:00:10,333
I wish I had not turned a blind
eye to the red flags

2
00:00:10,467 --> 00:00:11,867
I saw in you.

3
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:14,267
I would not have been hurt
like this.

4
00:00:14,400 --> 00:00:17,400
Marj, there's something
you should know.

5
00:00:17,533 --> 00:00:19,033
He wants to say there
is no longer any chance

6
00:00:19,167 --> 00:00:20,100
for us to reconcile.

7
00:00:20,233 --> 00:00:22,800
So stay out of my way,
my dear brother.

8
00:00:22,933 --> 00:00:24,267
Why did you not tell Marj?

9
00:00:24,400 --> 00:00:26,833
Do you understand now
why we did the same?

10
00:00:26,967 --> 00:00:29,267
I'm doing this
because I love my daughter.

11
00:00:29,400 --> 00:00:31,933
You did it,
because you hate yourself

12
00:00:32,067 --> 00:00:33,700
and nothing will ever
satisfy you.

13
00:00:33,867 --> 00:00:34,933
You are disgusting!

14
00:00:35,067 --> 00:00:36,267
You make me sick.

15
00:00:36,400 --> 00:00:40,300
Do what you think is right

16
00:00:40,433 --> 00:00:44,267
so you can be forgiven
by him and by your spouse.

17
00:00:45,633 --> 00:00:48,333
Marj, you and Jasmine should
leave this place too.

18
00:00:48,467 --> 00:00:50,167
You do not deserve
this kind of family.

19
00:00:50,300 --> 00:00:52,000
I really want to leave.

20
00:00:52,133 --> 00:00:55,467
Your HLA typing results are out.

21
00:00:55,600 --> 00:00:59,833
Unfortunately, you are not
a compatible match for Jasmine.

22
00:00:59,967 --> 00:01:02,000
Where will we find a donor?

23
00:01:02,133 --> 00:01:04,300
We need your help to see

24
00:01:04,433 --> 00:01:07,800
if there is a possible bone
marrow donor match

25
00:01:07,967 --> 00:01:08,767
for Jasmine.

26
00:01:08,900 --> 00:01:10,533
You are our best chance.

27
00:01:10,667 --> 00:01:13,167
I will not allow you
to include Ashley.

28
00:01:13,300 --> 00:01:15,067
Mom, but I want to try.

29
00:01:15,200 --> 00:01:18,533
Would it not be great
if I matched with Jasmine?

30
00:01:18,667 --> 00:01:20,800
Why can I not get tested?

31
00:01:22,200 --> 00:01:28,300
[DRAMATIC TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

32
00:01:28,433 --> 00:01:33,933
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

33
00:01:35,100 --> 00:01:39,100
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

34
00:01:41,567 --> 00:01:44,400
[DRAMATIC TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

35
00:01:45,967 --> 00:01:55,567
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

36
00:02:09,700 --> 00:02:14,567
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

37
00:02:21,800 --> 00:02:22,933
[SOBS]

38
00:02:29,033 --> 00:02:30,267
Ash?

39
00:02:33,100 --> 00:02:34,133
What's wrong?

40
00:02:35,567 --> 00:02:36,700
Nothing.

41
00:02:37,900 --> 00:02:41,200
Jasmine and I just had a small
misunderstanding.

42
00:02:45,833 --> 00:02:47,000
Let us go out.

43
00:02:50,400 --> 00:02:52,000
Where are we going?

44
00:02:54,133 --> 00:02:55,567
Somewhere...

45
00:02:56,633 --> 00:02:57,667
we can breathe.

46
00:02:58,867 --> 00:03:00,167
Away from everyone.

47
00:03:09,667 --> 00:03:10,900
I am sorry, my child.

48
00:03:13,100 --> 00:03:17,833
Maybe it is only now sinking in
for Edward

49
00:03:17,967 --> 00:03:19,533
about your affair with Thea.

50
00:03:21,267 --> 00:03:23,133
He almost killed you.

51
00:03:25,933 --> 00:03:26,900
Mom...

52
00:03:28,067 --> 00:03:29,433
I'm okay.

53
00:03:29,567 --> 00:03:31,000
Please go to Edward instead.

54
00:03:31,700 --> 00:03:33,400
He needs you more.

55
00:03:33,533 --> 00:03:35,333
He's not the one who's bleeding.

56
00:03:35,467 --> 00:03:37,967
He is not the one covered
in bruises, right?

57
00:03:41,433 --> 00:03:44,000
I missed bonding like this
with you.

58
00:03:44,133 --> 00:03:46,667
I wish every day we were just
like this.

59
00:03:46,800 --> 00:03:49,633
No problems,
everything just calm.

60
00:03:49,767 --> 00:03:50,967
I know.

61
00:03:51,100 --> 00:03:53,600
It was really a big mistake
that we came to Manila.

62
00:03:54,633 --> 00:03:56,967
I am really glad
you are still here with me.

63
00:03:58,000 --> 00:04:00,633
I might have already lost
Jasmine.

64
00:04:02,267 --> 00:04:03,233
My child, I am sorry...

65
00:04:04,267 --> 00:04:06,433
you are getting dragged
into all this chaos.

66
00:04:06,567 --> 00:04:09,133
You know, the last thing I want
is to see you get hurt.

67
00:04:10,300 --> 00:04:12,167
And you know Papa
loves you very much.

68
00:04:14,167 --> 00:04:17,300
But Dad, none of this
is your fault.

69
00:04:18,567 --> 00:04:20,933
But why does it feel like
everything is your fault?

70
00:04:22,100 --> 00:04:23,633
Is there another problem?

71
00:04:24,500 --> 00:04:25,767
I don't deserve you.

72
00:04:27,233 --> 00:04:28,267
What?

73
00:04:29,767 --> 00:04:31,500
You were right about Edward.

74
00:04:32,433 --> 00:04:33,967
That he is your favorite.

75
00:04:36,267 --> 00:04:39,700
Because I am bad.

76
00:04:42,233 --> 00:04:44,533
I am a useless sibling.

77
00:04:46,967 --> 00:04:48,700
I am a useless child.

78
00:04:50,200 --> 00:04:51,333
Paolo.

79
00:04:52,033 --> 00:04:53,667
Stop it with the self-pity.

80
00:04:54,700 --> 00:04:56,567
You are in no position
to tell me

81
00:04:56,700 --> 00:04:59,100
who my favorite should be.

82
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:03,167
I love you both equally.

83
00:05:05,833 --> 00:05:10,033
Whatever your mistakes are,
or your to sibling's,

84
00:05:10,167 --> 00:05:11,567
I'm not going to judge.

85
00:05:15,067 --> 00:05:16,133
[SIGHS]

86
00:05:16,267 --> 00:05:20,000
My child, Papa's mind is just
very troubled right now.

87
00:05:22,067 --> 00:05:25,067
I hate to do this right now,
but I think,

88
00:05:25,200 --> 00:05:27,400
I think I have to leave
the house for a while.

89
00:05:28,267 --> 00:05:29,400
I'm sorry.

90
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:32,000
What?

91
00:05:36,033 --> 00:05:37,800
I will go with you.

92
00:05:37,933 --> 00:05:39,467
Do not leave me in that house.

93
00:05:39,600 --> 00:05:42,933
My child, believe me, I want to
take you with me, but...

94
00:05:44,133 --> 00:05:45,600
is it not the middle
of the school year?

95
00:05:45,733 --> 00:05:47,733
I do not want your studies
to be affected.

96
00:05:48,700 --> 00:05:51,367
I think it's best if you stay
with the family first for now.

97
00:05:51,500 --> 00:05:54,033
But you were always the one
who judge others.

98
00:05:55,200 --> 00:05:58,967
That's because I know that they
cannot correct their mistakes.

99
00:06:01,333 --> 00:06:03,067
But I trust you.

100
00:06:04,233 --> 00:06:09,300
I trust that you can correct
your mistakes if you want.

101
00:06:11,067 --> 00:06:12,433
[PAOLO SOBS]

102
00:06:12,567 --> 00:06:20,700
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

103
00:06:20,833 --> 00:06:22,733
[SOBBING]

104
00:06:28,433 --> 00:06:30,233
It's okay.

105
00:06:31,733 --> 00:06:34,333
[SOBBING]

106
00:06:35,667 --> 00:06:37,000
I do not want!

107
00:06:37,133 --> 00:06:38,433
Do not leave me there.

108
00:06:38,567 --> 00:06:39,667
My child, listen to me first.

109
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:45,800
Just always remember,

110
00:06:45,933 --> 00:06:47,500
you are not doing anything
wrong.

111
00:06:49,033 --> 00:06:50,367
You did nothing wrong.

112
00:06:51,300 --> 00:06:57,233
Always remember that Papa
loves you very much.

113
00:06:58,600 --> 00:06:59,500
Stop crying now.

114
00:06:59,633 --> 00:07:00,733
Come

115
00:07:02,633 --> 00:07:03,900
Papa.

116
00:07:06,033 --> 00:07:11,833
[SOBBING]
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

117
00:07:19,967 --> 00:07:21,600
It's okay.

118
00:07:23,400 --> 00:07:25,600
This huge mistake
that you made...

119
00:07:27,100 --> 00:07:30,567
don't wait for your brother
to forgive you.

120
00:07:30,700 --> 00:07:33,267
You know he's got too much
pride for that.

121
00:07:34,800 --> 00:07:37,733
What you should do is act on

122
00:07:37,867 --> 00:07:40,600
what you think is right

123
00:07:40,733 --> 00:07:44,700
so you can be forgiven by them
and by your spouse.

124
00:07:47,133 --> 00:07:48,200
You can do this.

125
00:07:49,633 --> 00:07:51,000
I know you'll do
the right thing.

126
00:07:51,133 --> 00:07:53,300
I know, I know.

127
00:07:55,233 --> 00:07:59,867
- I love you so much.
- I love you.

128
00:08:14,900 --> 00:08:24,400
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

129
00:08:32,167 --> 00:08:33,900
So you are here.

130
00:08:34,033 --> 00:08:37,133
I will just get some things
and go back to the hospital.

131
00:08:42,067 --> 00:08:43,600
Did you and your sibling fight?

132
00:08:48,233 --> 00:08:49,467
I deserve it.

133
00:08:53,767 --> 00:08:56,600
Lately, I've been thinking...

134
00:08:56,767 --> 00:08:59,467
I wish I had listened
to your sibling Edward.

135
00:09:02,033 --> 00:09:04,300
I wish I had not ignored
the red flags

136
00:09:04,433 --> 00:09:05,900
I saw in you.

137
00:09:07,400 --> 00:09:09,267
It would not have come to this.

138
00:09:11,033 --> 00:09:13,367
I would not have been hurt
like this.

139
00:09:15,200 --> 00:09:18,867
<i> Do what you think is right</i>

140
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:21,900
<i>so your spouse can forgive you.</i>

141
00:09:25,367 --> 00:09:26,433
Marj.

142
00:09:31,100 --> 00:09:34,367
There's something
you should know.

143
00:09:34,500 --> 00:09:41,667
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

144
00:09:44,667 --> 00:09:46,533
Marj, I want you to know that

145
00:09:46,667 --> 00:09:48,067
He wants to say there
is no longer any chance

146
00:09:48,200 --> 00:09:49,133
for us to reconcile.

147
00:09:52,500 --> 00:09:54,667
I am cutting off our connection.

148
00:09:54,800 --> 00:09:56,600
He and I are through.

149
00:10:00,833 --> 00:10:04,433
My child, go to your room
for now.

150
00:10:04,600 --> 00:10:07,400
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

151
00:10:07,533 --> 00:10:08,900
Excuse me.

152
00:10:13,533 --> 00:10:15,033
- Edward.
- Let me finish.

153
00:10:15,167 --> 00:10:16,700
- What are you doing?
- Let me finish!

154
00:10:20,300 --> 00:10:21,867
I thought I was done being angry
about it.

155
00:10:23,067 --> 00:10:24,633
Their betrayal with Thea
against us?

156
00:10:26,167 --> 00:10:27,267
The pain?

157
00:10:28,367 --> 00:10:30,000
It's too much.

158
00:10:30,133 --> 00:10:31,633
It all built up inside me.

159
00:10:31,767 --> 00:10:32,833
That is why.

160
00:10:33,467 --> 00:10:34,667
I let it out on him.

161
00:10:35,667 --> 00:10:36,867
I lost control.

162
00:10:39,367 --> 00:10:40,867
I understand.

163
00:10:43,833 --> 00:10:46,333
So stay out of my way,
my dear brother.

164
00:10:47,533 --> 00:10:49,133
If you do not want us to come
to blows.

165
00:10:51,733 --> 00:10:53,833
I still have a lot of anger
to release.

166
00:10:54,767 --> 00:10:58,800
About sixteen years
worth of it.

167
00:10:58,933 --> 00:11:08,900
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

168
00:11:10,700 --> 00:11:19,633
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

169
00:11:22,467 --> 00:11:28,600
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

170
00:11:28,733 --> 00:11:30,067
You are still leaving?

171
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:35,267
Do you think I can stand you
being here,

172
00:11:35,400 --> 00:11:36,367
in one house,

173
00:11:36,500 --> 00:11:37,700
in the same room?

174
00:11:38,700 --> 00:11:41,633
Thea, I can't even bear
to look at you.

175
00:11:41,800 --> 00:11:44,167
You, Dad, and Paolo
are disgusting!

176
00:11:44,300 --> 00:11:45,433
You make me sick.

177
00:11:46,833 --> 00:11:48,200
I heard you earlier.

178
00:11:49,300 --> 00:11:50,967
Why did you not tell Marj?

179
00:11:53,067 --> 00:11:56,333
Don't think,
even for a little bit,

180
00:11:56,467 --> 00:11:59,033
that I did that to save you
and Paolo.

181
00:12:00,100 --> 00:12:01,567
I did that for Ashley.

182
00:12:02,733 --> 00:12:04,467
Because if Marj finds out,

183
00:12:04,600 --> 00:12:06,667
Ashley could learn
the truth too.

184
00:12:08,033 --> 00:12:09,467
And I do not want her
to get hurt.

185
00:12:10,733 --> 00:12:12,800
She doesn't deserve to get hurt
this way.

186
00:12:14,700 --> 00:12:16,667
So you still consider her
your child?

187
00:12:16,800 --> 00:12:18,100
She is.

188
00:12:18,233 --> 00:12:20,200
And will always be mine.

189
00:12:21,800 --> 00:12:23,133
And that's my decision.

190
00:12:23,933 --> 00:12:26,600
That is why I will do everything
to keep her from getting hurt.

191
00:12:27,333 --> 00:12:30,500
And not confuse her even more
because of your mess.

192
00:12:30,633 --> 00:12:32,467
I don't want to lie to her.

193
00:12:32,600 --> 00:12:35,533
But I'd rather keep her innocent
in all of this.

194
00:12:36,700 --> 00:12:39,433
So now you understand
why we did what we did?

195
00:12:39,567 --> 00:12:44,033
Don't you ever freaking use this
lie to justify

196
00:12:44,167 --> 00:12:46,267
the filth you and Paolo did!

197
00:12:49,567 --> 00:12:52,067
I'm doing this
because I love my daughter.

198
00:12:54,233 --> 00:12:57,633
You did it because you hate
yourself.

199
00:12:57,767 --> 00:12:59,767
And nothing will ever
satisfy you.

200
00:13:02,167 --> 00:13:03,600
Stay miserable, Thea.

201
00:13:05,233 --> 00:13:06,733
You deserve it.

202
00:13:06,867 --> 00:13:14,267
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

203
00:13:14,400 --> 00:13:18,867
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

204
00:13:20,367 --> 00:13:21,567
Edward.

205
00:13:30,100 --> 00:13:31,167
Ashley?

206
00:13:32,600 --> 00:13:34,000
Why are you crying?

207
00:13:34,933 --> 00:13:38,467
Ah, Papa said he's leaving.

208
00:13:38,600 --> 00:13:43,300
I did not want him to be hungry
on the way, so I prepared this.

209
00:13:44,967 --> 00:13:48,667
Auntie Marj,
please convince him to stay.

210
00:13:49,467 --> 00:13:53,067
I am trying, but I cannot change
Papa's mind anymore.

211
00:13:54,200 --> 00:13:56,700
Ashley, if that is your
father's decision...

212
00:13:57,900 --> 00:13:59,933
there is nothing I can do.

213
00:14:00,800 --> 00:14:02,800
- Auntie Marj.
- Edward, please.

214
00:14:02,933 --> 00:14:04,767
Don't do this again.

215
00:14:06,833 --> 00:14:11,200
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

216
00:14:11,333 --> 00:14:13,000
You are leaving again.

217
00:14:14,200 --> 00:14:16,367
You are leaving us again.

218
00:14:17,233 --> 00:14:21,267
Leaving will not solve
your problems.

219
00:14:21,400 --> 00:14:23,933
- [SOBBING]
- Mom, I will just call you,

220
00:14:24,067 --> 00:14:25,000
okay?

221
00:14:25,133 --> 00:14:26,867
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

222
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:28,233
Pa...

223
00:14:36,800 --> 00:14:38,100
Thank you.

224
00:14:39,567 --> 00:14:40,867
Can you just stay?

225
00:14:41,700 --> 00:14:43,367
Do not leave me here.

226
00:14:44,467 --> 00:14:46,033
[SIGHS]

227
00:14:46,833 --> 00:14:51,433
My child, take care
of yourself, okay?

228
00:14:51,567 --> 00:14:53,000
We'll see each other soon.

229
00:14:53,133 --> 00:14:54,567
I promise.

230
00:14:56,967 --> 00:14:59,133
[SOBBING]

231
00:14:59,267 --> 00:15:06,833
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

232
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:10,267
Mom, please take her back
to her room.

233
00:15:10,400 --> 00:15:11,667
I do not want to, Dad!

234
00:15:11,800 --> 00:15:13,767
[SOBBING]

235
00:15:13,900 --> 00:15:14,900
Dad!

236
00:15:15,033 --> 00:15:16,367
[SOBBING]

237
00:15:20,533 --> 00:15:22,000
Come on now, my grandchild.

238
00:15:24,833 --> 00:15:27,200
[SOBBING]

239
00:15:27,333 --> 00:15:34,900
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

240
00:15:38,367 --> 00:15:39,667
Where are you going?

241
00:15:42,967 --> 00:15:44,167
To Iloilo.

242
00:15:45,367 --> 00:15:47,900
I have a friend there who needs
help running a business,

243
00:15:48,033 --> 00:15:50,833
and it's a good opportunity.

244
00:15:50,967 --> 00:15:54,333
Edward, if this is about
what Paolo did to you,

245
00:15:54,467 --> 00:15:56,767
I will apologize for him.

246
00:15:56,900 --> 00:15:58,067
No.

247
00:15:59,167 --> 00:16:01,367
Marj, you did nothing wrong.

248
00:16:01,500 --> 00:16:02,900
We are both victims here.

249
00:16:03,033 --> 00:16:04,200
Don't apologize.

250
00:16:05,067 --> 00:16:07,033
Our spouses...

251
00:16:07,167 --> 00:16:08,933
are the ones
who caused us pain.

252
00:16:13,800 --> 00:16:15,400
You know, Marj, if I were you...

253
00:16:17,000 --> 00:16:18,767
you and Jasmine should leave
this place too.

254
00:16:20,567 --> 00:16:22,467
You do not deserve this kind
of family.

255
00:16:24,467 --> 00:16:26,500
But why leave Ashley?

256
00:16:27,467 --> 00:16:28,900
She'll have a better life here.

257
00:16:29,867 --> 00:16:31,233
With my parents...

258
00:16:32,300 --> 00:16:33,400
without me.

259
00:16:33,533 --> 00:16:34,767
Well, at least for now.

260
00:16:35,767 --> 00:16:38,767
I need to stay
in this house, Edward.

261
00:16:39,933 --> 00:16:42,300
Even though I really want
to leave.

262
00:16:43,833 --> 00:16:45,800
My child is critically ill.

263
00:16:45,933 --> 00:16:47,567
She cannot handle the stress

264
00:16:47,700 --> 00:16:49,500
if Paolo and I separate.

265
00:16:50,633 --> 00:16:52,100
She needs a complete family

266
00:16:52,233 --> 00:16:54,000
to stay strong.

267
00:16:55,000 --> 00:16:58,633
That is why I endure
and stay patient for her.

268
00:16:58,767 --> 00:17:04,367
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

269
00:17:04,500 --> 00:17:05,600
Marj.

270
00:17:06,733 --> 00:17:07,533
Marj.

271
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:11,433
I hope so.

272
00:17:12,333 --> 00:17:14,567
I hope you do not regret
your decision.

273
00:17:14,700 --> 00:17:23,267
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

274
00:17:26,533 --> 00:17:35,367
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

275
00:17:52,467 --> 00:17:56,167
Mr. and Mrs. Torrecampo,
good afternoon.

276
00:17:56,300 --> 00:17:57,800
I am Dr. Pascual.

277
00:17:57,933 --> 00:18:00,367
As discussed between you
and Dr. Alvarez,

278
00:18:00,500 --> 00:18:02,833
he will be transferring
your care to me temporarily

279
00:18:02,967 --> 00:18:04,500
while he's out of the country.

280
00:18:06,033 --> 00:18:10,133
Ah, your HLA typing results
are also out.

281
00:18:10,267 --> 00:18:15,033
Unfortunately, you are not
a compatible match for Jasmine.

282
00:18:16,133 --> 00:18:17,833
Does that mean we cannot donate?

283
00:18:18,967 --> 00:18:20,433
What will happen to my child?

284
00:18:20,567 --> 00:18:21,600
What will happen to her?

285
00:18:22,867 --> 00:18:24,167
- What is this?
- [STAMMERS]

286
00:18:24,300 --> 00:18:25,500
- If we are not a match,
- [STAMMERING]

287
00:18:25,633 --> 00:18:29,133
how will we find someone else
if they are not a match either?

288
00:18:29,267 --> 00:18:30,467
What will happen, Paolo?

289
00:18:30,600 --> 00:18:31,567
Tell me!

290
00:18:31,700 --> 00:18:33,200
Huh?

291
00:18:33,333 --> 00:18:35,367
Tell me, we promised Jasmine

292
00:18:35,500 --> 00:18:37,467
that everything would be okay.

293
00:18:37,600 --> 00:18:40,067
That she would get better,
but how will that happen

294
00:18:40,200 --> 00:18:41,567
if we cannot donate?

295
00:18:41,700 --> 00:18:44,000
Where will we find a donor?

296
00:18:44,133 --> 00:18:47,400
[SOBBING]

297
00:18:47,533 --> 00:18:48,700
We will ask others for help.

298
00:18:48,833 --> 00:18:50,033
We will not stop.

299
00:18:50,900 --> 00:18:53,867
[SOBBING]

300
00:18:54,000 --> 00:19:03,033
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

301
00:19:03,200 --> 00:19:04,667
This is not the end, Marj.

302
00:19:05,767 --> 00:19:07,467
We will find a donor.

303
00:19:07,600 --> 00:19:10,633
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

304
00:19:10,767 --> 00:19:13,700
The doctor said there
is a higher chance

305
00:19:13,833 --> 00:19:15,733
a match if
it is a blood relative.

306
00:19:19,267 --> 00:19:20,500
We are not giving up, okay?

307
00:19:23,467 --> 00:19:25,100
I will talk to Mom.

308
00:19:25,233 --> 00:19:28,967
I will convince everyone I know.

309
00:19:29,133 --> 00:19:30,333
I will beg if I have to.

310
00:19:30,467 --> 00:19:33,267
We will convince
your family too.

311
00:19:33,400 --> 00:19:34,900
I know.

312
00:19:35,033 --> 00:19:38,367
We will ask them
if they can get tested.

313
00:19:38,700 --> 00:19:41,233
Paolo, we are not just
asking them.

314
00:19:41,367 --> 00:19:43,267
We will convince them.

315
00:19:44,467 --> 00:19:47,167
None of them can refuse to help.

316
00:19:47,300 --> 00:19:53,967
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

317
00:20:01,333 --> 00:20:08,000
Ah, I know it's complicated
lately within the family,

318
00:20:08,167 --> 00:20:11,700
but Marj and I are here

319
00:20:11,833 --> 00:20:12,967
to ask for your help.

320
00:20:14,667 --> 00:20:16,567
Maybe we can all come together.

321
00:20:20,433 --> 00:20:21,833
Stop beating around the bush.

322
00:20:21,967 --> 00:20:23,700
What do you want?

323
00:20:23,833 --> 00:20:26,067
If it is all right with
everyone...

324
00:20:27,733 --> 00:20:30,467
we need your help.

325
00:20:30,600 --> 00:20:32,833
You need to get tested

326
00:20:32,967 --> 00:20:34,667
to see if there is a possible

327
00:20:34,800 --> 00:20:37,567
bone marrow donor match
for Jasmine.

328
00:20:38,733 --> 00:20:39,700
They told us

329
00:20:39,833 --> 00:20:41,467
the chances are higher
with blood relatives...

330
00:20:42,567 --> 00:20:44,133
specifically siblings.

331
00:20:46,000 --> 00:20:48,133
And because Jasmine
is an only child...

332
00:20:49,433 --> 00:20:51,467
you are our best chance.

333
00:20:53,867 --> 00:20:56,100
Stop the dramatics.

334
00:20:56,233 --> 00:20:58,267
Of course I will get tested
for my grandchild.

335
00:21:03,167 --> 00:21:05,700
We'll all get tested.

336
00:21:05,833 --> 00:21:06,733
You too, Thea.

337
00:21:06,867 --> 00:21:08,267
And of course, Ashley as well.

338
00:21:12,967 --> 00:21:14,833
I have no problem getting
tested.

339
00:21:16,967 --> 00:21:19,800
But I will not allow you
to include Ashley in this.

340
00:21:21,533 --> 00:21:22,600
What?

341
00:21:23,767 --> 00:21:25,700
But Mom, I want to help Jasmine.

342
00:21:25,833 --> 00:21:27,633
Why can I not get tested?

343
00:21:27,767 --> 00:21:33,100
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

344
00:21:33,233 --> 00:21:42,200
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

345
00:21:43,600 --> 00:21:46,400
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

346
00:21:48,300 --> 00:21:51,267
Wouldn't it be great
if I matched with Jasmine?

347
00:21:51,933 --> 00:21:54,167
No! It's not great!

348
00:21:54,300 --> 00:21:55,600
You are still a minor, right?

349
00:21:58,067 --> 00:21:59,333
Do you even know
how dangerous procedures

350
00:21:59,467 --> 00:22:02,033
like that can be for a donor?

351
00:22:04,567 --> 00:22:05,900
[SCOFFS]

352
00:22:06,033 --> 00:22:09,467
Look, I know I may not look
like it,

353
00:22:09,600 --> 00:22:11,667
but I am concerned
about Jasmine too.

354
00:22:12,167 --> 00:22:14,367
I have also been reading
about her illness.

355
00:22:15,200 --> 00:22:17,467
And procedures may carry serious
risks for the donor

356
00:22:17,633 --> 00:22:20,100
that harvest bone marrow.

357
00:22:20,767 --> 00:22:22,833
Thea, I'm sure
it's pretty low risk.

358
00:22:22,967 --> 00:22:24,833
But Mom, there is still risk.

359
00:22:24,967 --> 00:22:28,600
Mom, Thea is right.

360
00:22:30,433 --> 00:22:33,433
The probability is low anyway
because they are cousins.

361
00:22:34,833 --> 00:22:38,767
So let us not risk Ashley's
health.

362
00:22:40,033 --> 00:22:42,667
Mom, but I want to try.

363
00:22:42,800 --> 00:22:44,733
I really want to help Jasmine.

364
00:22:45,500 --> 00:22:51,433
Ash, I know you can help her
in some other way.

365
00:22:54,567 --> 00:22:56,433
There's plenty of us here
to help.

366
00:22:56,567 --> 00:22:58,567
If none of us match,

367
00:22:58,700 --> 00:23:00,300
then we'll find other people.

368
00:23:00,433 --> 00:23:02,967
We are not going to abandon
my grandchild, right?

369
00:23:03,900 --> 00:23:04,900
Oh?

370
00:23:05,033 --> 00:23:13,267
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

371
00:23:13,400 --> 00:23:16,500
But Mom, why can I not
just get tested?

372
00:23:16,633 --> 00:23:18,400
There is nothing wrong with it.

373
00:23:19,033 --> 00:23:20,467
Ashley, what is this?

374
00:23:20,600 --> 00:23:22,400
We already decided on this,
right?

375
00:23:22,567 --> 00:23:24,867
When I say no, it will not
happen.

376
00:23:26,333 --> 00:23:29,033
You decided, Mom,

377
00:23:29,167 --> 00:23:31,133
but I was not included
in that decision.

378
00:23:33,067 --> 00:23:35,867
Wait, what are you really angry
about?

379
00:23:36,000 --> 00:23:38,133
That you cannot help
your cousin?

380
00:23:38,933 --> 00:23:41,767
That she is not paying attention
to you anymore, right?

381
00:23:41,900 --> 00:23:44,900
What, is she joining her
mother's anger against us?

382
00:23:45,033 --> 00:23:48,467
Then she should not expect
to get anything from us!

383
00:23:49,000 --> 00:23:50,900
Besides, her mother already said

384
00:23:51,033 --> 00:23:53,300
it is fine if you do not
get tested.

385
00:23:53,433 --> 00:23:55,633
So, can you please stop
pushing this?

386
00:23:55,800 --> 00:24:00,933
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

387
00:24:03,200 --> 00:24:07,700
Mom, Jasmine needs our help more
than anything right now.

388
00:24:08,967 --> 00:24:10,933
If you want to make amends
with Auntie Marj

389
00:24:11,067 --> 00:24:13,133
for what you did to her,

390
00:24:13,267 --> 00:24:16,367
you will help them through me.

391
00:24:16,500 --> 00:24:21,267
You do not speak about things
you know nothing about!

392
00:24:21,967 --> 00:24:24,367
Ashley, these are adult issues.

393
00:24:24,900 --> 00:24:26,300
You should not get involved!

394
00:24:30,767 --> 00:24:32,267
I am so sorry, Mom.

395
00:24:33,533 --> 00:24:35,000
I didn't mean to.

396
00:24:37,567 --> 00:24:40,300
I just really wanted
to help Jasmine.

397
00:24:43,667 --> 00:24:44,667
[SIGHS]

398
00:24:46,733 --> 00:24:50,700
My child, let me be clear.

399
00:24:51,333 --> 00:24:54,267
It is not that I am stopping you
from helping.

400
00:24:55,367 --> 00:24:57,600
Again, I am just worried
about you.

401
00:24:58,767 --> 00:25:00,200
Even if you ask your father,

402
00:25:00,333 --> 00:25:02,700
he would not agree either.

403
00:25:02,867 --> 00:25:06,600
So please, let Jasmine be
for now.

404
00:25:06,733 --> 00:25:08,700
They will find someone
to help them.

405
00:25:08,833 --> 00:25:15,500
[DRAMATIC TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

406
00:25:15,633 --> 00:25:25,133
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

407
00:25:28,600 --> 00:25:35,633
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

408
00:25:35,800 --> 00:25:37,400
Mr. and Mrs. Torrecampo,

409
00:25:37,533 --> 00:25:38,967
I just want to update you

410
00:25:39,100 --> 00:25:41,133
that since there is still
no match for Jasmine,

411
00:25:41,267 --> 00:25:44,200
what we can do is make sure
she remains stable

412
00:25:44,333 --> 00:25:45,933
and free from infection.

413
00:25:46,067 --> 00:25:49,267
But there is a time pressure.

414
00:25:49,400 --> 00:25:50,667
What do you mean po?

415
00:25:50,800 --> 00:25:51,967
Are you joking?

416
00:25:52,100 --> 00:25:55,333
Do you want me to take back
your dismissal?

417
00:25:55,467 --> 00:25:57,033
I am not leaving.

418
00:25:57,167 --> 00:25:58,833
Do not force me, Greg.

419
00:25:58,967 --> 00:26:00,433
Otherwise, I will expose

420
00:26:00,567 --> 00:26:02,267
all the dirt I know,

421
00:26:02,400 --> 00:26:04,100
especially about you.

422
00:26:06,200 --> 00:26:07,733
Are you threatening me?

423
00:26:07,867 --> 00:26:10,200
Yes, Sir Greg.

424
00:26:10,367 --> 00:26:14,400
My God, please grant my one
and only request

425
00:26:14,733 --> 00:26:17,300
I hope we find a donor soon

426
00:26:17,433 --> 00:26:19,067
so Jasmine can recover.

427
00:26:19,200 --> 00:26:21,167
I love my child very much.

428
00:26:21,300 --> 00:26:23,567
You are really different from
this family.

429
00:26:23,700 --> 00:26:24,867
You are a good child.

430
00:26:25,000 --> 00:26:26,700
Tell me, Ma'am Marj,

431
00:26:26,833 --> 00:26:29,867
maybe there is something
I can do

432
00:26:30,000 --> 00:26:31,600
to repay your kindness to me.

433
00:26:33,000 --> 00:26:34,300
But it is such a pity, right?

434
00:26:34,433 --> 00:26:36,167
I wish Jasmine had a sibling.

435
00:26:36,300 --> 00:26:39,533
Because would that not make
things easier for her, my child?

436
00:26:39,667 --> 00:26:42,267
Would there be a higher chance
of a match?

437
00:26:42,433 --> 00:26:43,567
Am I right?

438
00:26:43,700 --> 00:26:45,400
There will surely be one

439
00:26:45,533 --> 00:26:48,100
If it were possible
to ask every family

440
00:26:48,233 --> 00:26:49,867
in the world, they would do it.

441
00:26:50,000 --> 00:26:51,700
In this very house,

442
00:26:51,833 --> 00:26:54,100
there is one person
who has not yet been checked

443
00:26:54,233 --> 00:26:56,167
for a match with Jasmine.

444
00:26:56,300 --> 00:26:57,667
There is still hope, Ma'am Marj.

445
00:26:57,800 --> 00:26:59,000
Hello, Yolly?

446
00:26:59,133 --> 00:27:00,633
I would like to talk to you.

447
00:27:00,767 --> 00:27:03,000
You need to know the truth.

448
00:27:03,133 --> 00:27:04,367
What truth?
